dcterms:creator: W. O. Kermack
A. G. McKendrick
dcterms:description: The SIR model is a classical epidemiological compartmental model that describes the spread of infectious diseases through the Susceptible, Infected, and Recovered compartments in a population.
dcterms:title: SIR Model

dcterms:creator: Craig W Reynolds
dcterms:description: Reynold's Boids model is a distributed behavioral model that simulates the flocking behavior of birds, showcasing emergent properties through simple local rules.
dcterms:title: Reynold’s Boids Model

dcterms:creator: Giovanni Dalmasso
Paula Andrea Marin Zapata
Nathan Ryan Brady
Anne Hamacher-Brady
dcterms:description: Dalmasso’s Mitochondria Model is an agent-based model that links sub-cellular dynamics to cellular homeostasis and heterogeneity, focusing on the behavior of mitochondria within a cell.
dcterms:title: Dalmasso’s Mitochondria Model
